Description: Two sherds (one of two joining fragments) of body of Attic pottery closed vessel, probably oenochoe; inside reserved; outside, vertical glazed area covered in added red on right of 396b+c (clothed figure?); incised inscription in four lines to left.
Bibliographic references: Gardner 1888 / Naukratis II (p. 66, no. 819, pl. XXI, no. 819)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 688, no. 468)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.2057)
